LEGIONELLOSIS - GERMANY (02): (NORTH RHINE-WESTPHALIA) UPDATE
*************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 26 Sep 2014
Source: Radio Rur [in German, machine trans.] edited]
http://www.radiorur.de/rur/rr/1237715/news/kreis_dueren%3Ehttp://www.radiorur.de/rur/rr/1237715/news/kreis_dueren


The origin of the legionellosis outbreak in Juelich might be the Forschungszentrum. [Forschungszentrum is a scientific research institute in Juelich (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Forschungszentrum_Jülich#Location).]

Initial investigations have found large numbers of _Legionella_ in the water from one of its cooling towers. Further tests will show whether the cooling system is responsible for the legionnaires' disease outbreak in Juelich. The cooling tower has been shut down and will be disinfected. Two other cooling towers at the research centre are free of _Legionella_. According to the local health authorities, the experts are surprised, as the facility is in good condition.

Over the last weeks, the number of suspected cases of legionellosis has risen to 60, of which 23 cases have been confirmed so far, while 20 tested negative. The laboratory results are pending for 17 other cases. All of the patients had pneumonia. The investigation has been ongoing for a week; the last confirmed infection occurred 10 days ago.

Samples are being taken from the [respiratory tract of patients] in an attempt to identify the pathogen and compare it to reference strains. Samples have also been taken from the research facility, as well as from other sources, such as sewage treatment plants, wastewater ponds, and streams.

